.TH SIMPLE_SHELL
.SH PROLOG
This manual page is part of the Holberton School Simple Shell Project. It can differ from other shell projects due to its simpler functionality.
.SH SHELL
interactive:
./hsh - $[command] [argument]
non-interactive:
[command] [argument]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B corrupt
[\fB\-n\fR \fIBITS\fR]
[\fB\-\-bits\fR \fIBITS\fR]
.IR file ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B corrupt
modifies files by toggling a randomly chosen bit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-bits =\fIBITS\fR
Set the number of bits to modify.
Default is one bit.
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Tahir Alizade <jamesalfreddie@gmail.com>
.SH BUG REPORTS
Report bugs to <jamesalfreddie@gmail.com>

